WEBVTT

00:36.266 --> 00:39.060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

00:46.526 --> 00:48.152
SISTER VENGEANCE

00:50.613 --> 00:52.115
S#38 SEOK-GU'S HOUSE - FRONT - DAY

01:13.428 --> 01:14.888
Damn it.

01:47.211 --> 01:52.133
1F: AGIT
2F: KOPARK FILM PRODUCTION

02:00.683 --> 02:02.977
Why are you writing again already?

02:03.061 --> 02:04.604
Your movie premieres in a few days.

02:09.359 --> 02:10.193
Hear me out.

02:11.110 --> 02:13.780
There's this thing called
the National Stress Management Department.

02:14.280 --> 02:15.281
They're public officials.

02:17.242 --> 02:20.036
Their job is to take out idiots
who stress out citizens.

02:20.995 --> 02:22.747
And by that, I mean kill.

02:23.539 --> 02:24.374
That's amusing.

02:24.457 --> 02:27.835
But they don't kill randomly.
It's based on an intricate system.

02:27.919 --> 02:29.295
This system has found

02:30.421 --> 02:32.924
that far more people die from stress

02:33.591 --> 02:37.929
caused by idiots they can't stand
than from wars or natural disasters.

02:38.012 --> 02:40.348
The second they open their mouths,
it pisses off the entire country.

02:40.431 --> 02:42.684
Their looks, their words,
and their laughter piss everyone off.

02:43.393 --> 02:44.644
Right, people like that exist.

02:44.727 --> 02:47.939
Because of them, people are dying
from high blood pressure or heart attacks,

02:48.022 --> 02:50.900
causing major economic losses
for the country.

02:51.484 --> 02:54.570
So now, it's become standard practice
for society to eliminate these idiots.

02:55.154 --> 02:57.031
The system monitors everyone,

02:57.115 --> 03:00.660
and the moment someone
hits that threshold…

03:05.331 --> 03:06.290
The siren goes off.

03:08.042 --> 03:09.335
NATIONAL STRESS MANAGEMENT DEPARTMENT

03:10.294 --> 03:12.839
And the name of the target appears.

03:12.922 --> 03:14.340
HWANG DONG-MAN

03:15.341 --> 03:19.012
Then the NSMD is dispatched
and must kill that person within 24 hours.

03:20.179 --> 03:21.472
No matter where they are,

03:22.306 --> 03:23.558
they must hunt them down…

03:26.936 --> 03:28.563
and shoot them!

03:45.455 --> 03:46.748
They even make an official statement.

03:46.831 --> 03:52.462
"At 0100 hours, Hwang, a Seoul resident,
was eliminated by the NSMD."

03:52.545 --> 03:54.047
There's no public backlash either.

03:54.589 --> 03:57.884
A few politicians have been eliminated
this way, so everyone is on edge.

03:57.967 --> 03:59.844
They analyze what pisses off citizens,

03:59.927 --> 04:03.014
such as their tone or facial expressions.

04:03.639 --> 04:04.640
They even get lessons

04:05.224 --> 04:08.061
on how to speak without offending people
and to become likable.

04:08.644 --> 04:09.687
That sounds amusing.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.522
There's action, comedy,

04:12.523 --> 04:13.691
and room for a dilemma.

04:13.775 --> 04:15.693
There's no dilemma. I just kill them off.

04:15.777 --> 04:18.571
Come on, it's a movie. You need a dilemma.

04:18.654 --> 04:21.574
Don't get too caught up
with Hwang Dong-man.

04:26.871 --> 04:29.540
I was so pissed at Hwang Dong-man
that I couldn't sleep

04:29.624 --> 04:30.792
and ended up with this.

04:33.961 --> 04:35.671
What should I do about that bastard?

04:35.755 --> 04:38.966
In a way, Hwang Dong-man is… your muse.

04:39.050 --> 04:40.259
A muse who pisses you off.

04:41.469 --> 04:43.096
When people reach our age,

04:43.179 --> 04:45.932
there's nothing we really like or hate,

04:46.015 --> 04:47.433
so there's nothing to write about.

04:47.517 --> 04:50.019
We feel emotionally drained.

04:50.103 --> 04:53.398
But this bastard comes along,
stirs things up, pisses you off,

04:53.481 --> 04:55.691
and suddenly you're writing something new.

04:56.442 --> 05:00.321
-Maybe you should be thanking--
-Hey, people are meant to be inspiring,

05:00.405 --> 05:01.447
not infuriating.

05:02.490 --> 05:03.950
What happened this time?

05:06.786 --> 05:08.621
Whatever it is,
I'm sure it won't surprise me.

05:08.704 --> 05:09.831
It won't.

05:16.337 --> 05:17.296
If I tell you…

05:19.882 --> 05:22.552
it'll piss me off
because I'll come off as a pathetic loser,

05:23.469 --> 05:24.846
but I want to tell you anyway.

05:26.889 --> 05:29.350
We all went to
Director Choi's kimchi stew restaurant.

05:29.434 --> 05:30.685
-Welcome.
-Welcome.

05:31.185 --> 05:33.187
But he said he didn't like kimchi stew.

05:35.022 --> 05:37.233
He went to a kimchi stew restaurant
on opening day,

05:37.316 --> 05:39.026
only to say he didn't like kimchi stew.

05:39.110 --> 05:40.736
He said he didn't like spicy food.

05:40.820 --> 05:41.863
I don't like spicy food.

05:41.946 --> 05:44.115
The bastard usually shovels down
whatever is in front of him,

05:44.198 --> 05:46.033
but he acted like
he couldn't eat spicy food.

05:46.117 --> 05:48.369
It was ridiculous.
He just didn't like what we were having.

05:48.452 --> 05:49.871
We can ask them to make it mild.

05:50.496 --> 05:53.124
-One mild kimchi stew, please.
-Okay.

05:53.207 --> 05:55.793
I didn't want that jerk
to get what he wanted to eat.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.753
This is what annoys me.

05:57.837 --> 06:00.047
Dealing with that bastard
makes me act pathetic too!

06:01.132 --> 06:04.135
After that, he sat there all pissed off,
stuffing his face.

06:08.431 --> 06:09.557
More bean sprouts, please!

06:09.640 --> 06:10.683
The bean sprouts aren't spicy.

06:11.726 --> 06:15.605
Do we really have to make a big deal
over food at our age?

06:16.272 --> 06:18.357
I was getting really fed up with him.

06:20.026 --> 06:21.861
He said he spent ten years preparing that.

06:21.944 --> 06:24.906
At the second place we went to,
he ordered whatever he wanted

06:24.989 --> 06:27.200
and just talked nonstop.

06:27.283 --> 06:28.117
You see,

06:28.951 --> 06:32.371
I'm a guy with a massive desire
to make people laugh with funny stories.

06:32.455 --> 06:34.290
I always prepare funny stories
wherever I go.

06:34.373 --> 06:36.542
The thought of making people laugh
excites me.

06:36.626 --> 06:38.169
But whenever he's around,

06:38.920 --> 06:41.756
all that desire goes right out the window.

06:43.216 --> 06:44.592
Being around him

06:44.675 --> 06:47.386
is nothing but getting through an ordeal.

06:48.179 --> 06:49.597
I just don't get it.

06:51.933 --> 06:52.767
Hey.

06:52.850 --> 06:55.561
Park said I didn't look like someone
about to release a movie.

06:55.645 --> 06:58.981
Was I supposed to explain in detail
how that bastard ruined my mood?

06:59.941 --> 07:01.025
I was tired, so I just said…

07:01.108 --> 07:01.984
It's just…

07:02.485 --> 07:04.278
I have a feeling the movie won't do well.

07:04.904 --> 07:06.405
That it might tank.

07:06.489 --> 07:09.867
That's when that damn bastard,
who was sitting way across the table,

07:09.951 --> 07:12.328
somehow heard what I said,

07:12.411 --> 07:14.538
and his face suddenly brightened up.

07:15.331 --> 07:16.332
Gyeong-se.

07:16.832 --> 07:18.459
Keep that up, and you'll end up like me.

07:19.919 --> 07:21.671
How? Why?

07:22.255 --> 07:23.965
I have my fifth movie coming out.

07:24.048 --> 07:27.593
So how the hell would I end up like him
when he hasn't even made his debut?

07:28.177 --> 07:29.929
That's Hwang Dong-man's go-to line.

07:30.429 --> 07:32.265
"Keep that up, and you'll end up like me."

07:32.348 --> 07:35.268
He acts self-deprecating
but implies no one is different from him.

07:35.351 --> 07:36.561
I'm totally different!

07:36.644 --> 07:38.521
While he was busy bad-mouthing others,

07:38.604 --> 07:41.649
I put up with all kinds of insults
and worked my ass off to get here!

07:41.732 --> 07:43.025
I worked hard so I could say,

07:43.109 --> 07:44.485
"I'll show you!"

07:45.236 --> 07:47.989
"I'll prove that I'm nothing like you!"

07:48.739 --> 07:50.866
Who does he think he is,

07:50.950 --> 07:53.411
trying to ride along
and acting like he's on my level?

07:53.494 --> 07:56.581
Obviously, I didn't actually think
my movie would tank, but…

07:56.664 --> 07:58.374
Keep that up, and you'll end up like me.

08:00.543 --> 08:01.502
He looked delighted.

08:02.628 --> 08:03.963
Incredibly delighted.

08:04.046 --> 08:05.298
I'm wondering

08:05.381 --> 08:08.259
if Dong-man should take an IQ test.

08:08.342 --> 08:11.887
If life keeps kicking you down,
does your intelligence go down with it?

08:11.971 --> 08:14.599
He's becoming less self-aware
and more out of control.

08:14.682 --> 08:16.475
That bastard has always been dumb.

08:16.559 --> 08:19.895
That's why he can't even
piss people off properly.

08:19.979 --> 08:24.108
All he can do is irritate you
in this lingering way.

08:24.609 --> 08:26.861
If he were actually smart and ruthless,

08:26.944 --> 08:30.615
we'd at least have a proper
head-to-head fight and cut ties clean.

08:30.698 --> 08:31.616
But with him?

08:31.699 --> 08:35.077
It's that same lingering irritation
my whole life.

08:35.161 --> 08:38.831
Twenty years
of the same damn lingering irritation.

08:38.914 --> 08:41.667
Shouldn't the government
take care of people like him?

08:41.751 --> 08:43.210
They need to shoot him like this.

09:04.273 --> 09:05.274
Damn it.

09:45.314 --> 09:49.026
Bigfin reef squid tend to bite

09:49.110 --> 09:51.862
when the lure starts to sink
right after the cast.

09:51.946 --> 09:53.406
When they bite, the fishing line…

09:58.327 --> 10:00.454
During the day,
leave the fishing line alone…

10:04.417 --> 10:06.961
Patience is the key.
Impatient people tend to…

10:11.340 --> 10:13.509
Damn it. Hey, Unit 308!

10:23.561 --> 10:24.603
Unit 308!

10:25.104 --> 10:27.606
You'd better pay
the maintenance fee by today!

10:27.690 --> 10:28.983
-Or I'll force your door open
-My wallet.

10:29.066 --> 10:30.443
and move all your stuff out!

10:31.152 --> 10:32.445
Do you understand?

10:34.572 --> 10:35.573
CHEONGRAM WRITING ACADEMY

10:35.656 --> 10:37.908
Why are we losing students by the day?

10:39.368 --> 10:41.078
This won't even cover the heating bill.

10:42.455 --> 10:43.581
Take out some ads, then.

10:44.790 --> 10:48.627
We advertise by putting up banners
with a long list of winners.

10:48.711 --> 10:51.338
So how can we do that
when we don't have a single winner?

10:52.131 --> 10:55.176
Bring your fancy director friends here

10:55.259 --> 10:58.220
and have them give
special lectures or something.

10:58.304 --> 11:00.514
Don't just talk about
how close you are to them.

11:03.350 --> 11:05.186
I can't bring them to a place like this.

11:06.020 --> 11:06.896
"A place like this"?

11:14.195 --> 11:15.404
You're not rich, are you?

11:16.947 --> 11:17.865
You've never seen one?

11:19.950 --> 11:21.285
Then why'd you write about them?

11:21.368 --> 11:23.412
It shows when you write from imagination.

11:23.496 --> 11:26.207
I can tell it's fake
because of the lack of details.

11:26.290 --> 11:28.792
But most of all,
watching how the rich live isn't fun.

11:28.876 --> 11:30.294
Why look at delicate, sheltered flowers?

11:30.377 --> 11:31.879
You snap its stem, but it still won't die.

11:31.962 --> 11:34.006
You burn it with a torch,
and it still won't die.

11:34.089 --> 11:36.509
A stubborn will to survive.
That's what makes a movie.

11:36.592 --> 11:39.178
Rich kids don't panic
when they get into trouble.

11:39.261 --> 11:40.095
They just make a call.

11:41.931 --> 11:42.765
"Daddy."

11:42.848 --> 11:44.517
They have adults
who clean up their messes.

11:44.600 --> 11:46.977
But kids who never had
that kind of support,

11:47.061 --> 11:48.062
their hearts drop.

11:48.145 --> 11:49.605
They have to handle it on their own.

11:49.688 --> 11:51.106
That's what a real movie is.

11:51.190 --> 11:54.109
People who do whatever it takes
to handle things on their own.

11:54.193 --> 11:55.694
Who can bring these characters to life?

12:00.908 --> 12:02.076
All right, everyone.

12:02.576 --> 12:07.122
Poverty is something etched
into every cell of your body.

12:07.206 --> 12:08.707
It's not something you can learn.

12:08.791 --> 12:10.876
Perseverance born from poverty

12:11.502 --> 12:12.962
makes you very perceptive.

12:13.045 --> 12:16.090
We examine every single shoe
at the doorway.

12:16.173 --> 12:17.967
Survival instincts force us to notice.

12:18.050 --> 12:21.428
We also read people's moods
just to get by.

12:21.512 --> 12:24.598
Think about it, Myeong-hun.
This is an incredible gift for a writer.

12:24.682 --> 12:25.683
Are you listening?

12:27.059 --> 12:28.686
Jeez, what am I going to do with you?

12:32.022 --> 12:34.942
For a writer,
poverty is a blessing sent by the gods.

12:35.776 --> 12:37.278
Don't write it down. Just listen.

12:38.237 --> 12:39.530
What is poverty for a writer?

12:39.613 --> 12:41.448
-A blessing sent by the gods.
-A blessing sent by the gods.

12:41.532 --> 12:44.285
Why would you throw away such a blessing
and write about something else?

12:44.368 --> 12:45.869
Rich people don't have this gift.

12:45.953 --> 12:49.582
They have zero awareness,
and they half-ass just about everything.

12:49.665 --> 12:51.000
You think they can write anything real?

12:52.001 --> 12:53.127
What about you, Mr. Hwang?

12:54.420 --> 12:55.629
Are you rich or poor?

12:56.297 --> 12:57.131
Me?

12:59.008 --> 13:00.509
I'm the definition of poor.

13:01.802 --> 13:03.429
Then why haven't you succeeded?

13:11.312 --> 13:12.438
What about you, Mr. Hwang?

13:13.647 --> 13:15.065
Then why haven't you succeeded?

13:39.673 --> 13:41.925
Guess what popped up on my emotion watch?

13:43.052 --> 13:44.303
Come on, take a guess.

13:45.929 --> 13:46.764
"Flustered"?

13:47.348 --> 13:48.182
"Offended"?

13:48.682 --> 13:49.516
"Anger"?

13:51.935 --> 13:52.770
Nope.

13:55.606 --> 13:56.440
"Resentful."

13:56.523 --> 13:58.567
RESENTFUL

13:58.651 --> 14:00.611
It's scary how accurate this is.

14:02.946 --> 14:04.239
I truly feel resentful.

14:11.455 --> 14:12.289
Fuck.

14:12.373 --> 14:13.832
LOAN SHARK

14:21.965 --> 14:22.800
Hello?

14:22.883 --> 14:26.095
Debtors in South Korea
are such great actors.

14:26.178 --> 14:28.889
When they borrow money,
they cry their eyes out,

14:28.973 --> 14:32.309
swear they'll repay the kindness,
and treat me like I'm their savior.

14:32.393 --> 14:34.895
But once they get the money,
they act like I don't exist anymore.

14:34.979 --> 14:38.148
The worst debtors are the ones
who cry and whine the most.

14:38.232 --> 14:39.566
But I don't make exceptions.

14:40.150 --> 14:41.402
Mr. Hwang Dong-man.

14:41.485 --> 14:43.112
Did your cat make it?

14:43.195 --> 14:45.781
How did the surgery go?

14:45.864 --> 14:49.159
Do I have to pay your cat a visit?

14:57.543 --> 15:01.130
Here's to Director Park Gyeong-se,
member of The Eight Club,

15:02.006 --> 15:05.175
and the release of his fifth movie,
Sister Vengeance.

15:07.177 --> 15:08.387
This brings back memories.

15:09.430 --> 15:11.140
I still remember

15:12.057 --> 15:13.934
the jealousy in everyone's eyes

15:14.393 --> 15:15.602
when I made my directorial debut.

15:17.396 --> 15:19.314
In the end, all of us have…

15:24.153 --> 15:25.362
Dong-man isn't here.

15:27.948 --> 15:29.950
I don't have to watch what I say, then.

15:31.410 --> 15:33.245
I felt my stomach drop.

15:35.080 --> 15:35.956
Now all of us

15:36.665 --> 15:38.542
have made our debuts

15:39.460 --> 15:40.961
and made all these movies.

15:41.545 --> 15:44.465
Now, we're big-shot directors
and producers,

15:44.548 --> 15:48.510
and everyone in the film industry
knows of The Eight Club.

15:49.553 --> 15:50.387
I'm so proud of us.

15:51.013 --> 15:55.976
So there was no reason for you jerks
to be so jealous of me back then.

15:58.020 --> 16:00.314
Director Park, how about a toast?

16:03.067 --> 16:06.070
So far, we've let the drinks flow,

16:06.153 --> 16:11.408
but the things we truly want
have never flowed in.

16:11.492 --> 16:13.994
So here's to getting everything
we want to flow in.

16:14.078 --> 16:15.245
Let the drinks flow!

16:15.329 --> 16:16.830
Let the writing flow!

16:16.914 --> 16:19.166
Let the money flow!

16:19.249 --> 16:21.460
And let the piss flow!

16:21.543 --> 16:24.546
-Let it flow!
-Let it flow!

16:25.964 --> 16:30.344
AGIT

16:31.887 --> 16:33.180
Welcome, sir.

16:42.189 --> 16:43.148
Man, seriously.

16:45.984 --> 16:47.569
-Hey, you're here.
-Take a seat.

16:54.368 --> 16:56.537
-Sounds like marketing is going well.
-I know, right?

16:56.620 --> 16:58.831
The title definitely pulled people in.

16:58.914 --> 17:03.335
I think Gyeong-se is the best in Korea
when it comes to creating amazing titles.

17:03.418 --> 17:05.212
Was that your idea, Director Park?

17:05.796 --> 17:06.672
Yes.

17:07.506 --> 17:09.424
I was really impressed.

17:12.469 --> 17:14.263
Wine glasses break easily. Take it away.

17:28.110 --> 17:28.944
Why aren't you eating?

17:29.528 --> 17:31.113
-Are you going to eat that?
-No, go ahead.

17:34.199 --> 17:35.242
You'll get indigestion.

17:35.993 --> 17:37.411
Slow down.

17:45.169 --> 17:47.588
Hey. Jeez, come on.

17:52.009 --> 17:55.470
Dong-man, when will you stop
fighting with food?

17:56.263 --> 17:58.473
You still attack everything on your plate.

18:02.936 --> 18:03.979
How are you these days?

18:04.897 --> 18:05.981
I'm really busy.

18:06.481 --> 18:07.858
I've got to watch lousy movies,

18:07.941 --> 18:10.819
and go around
roasting the hell out of it online.

18:11.486 --> 18:12.654
If I come across a good one,

18:12.738 --> 18:15.574
I spend a few days crying my eyes out

18:15.657 --> 18:17.159
from sheer jealousy.

18:18.493 --> 18:20.579
There just isn't enough time in a day.

18:22.706 --> 18:24.333
Sounds like you're really busy.

18:26.793 --> 18:28.086
Hold on.

18:28.170 --> 18:30.088
Is this that thing?

18:30.172 --> 18:31.340
Yes!

18:31.423 --> 18:33.842
I almost died because of this bastard!

18:33.926 --> 18:35.260
Dong-man, why bring that up again?

18:35.344 --> 18:36.595
Seriously,

18:36.678 --> 18:39.389
I almost died of a heart attack.

18:39.473 --> 18:41.683
He said his younger brother
was developing a watch

18:41.767 --> 18:43.685
and needed some volunteers or something.

18:43.769 --> 18:45.729
Hey, where are you going?

18:45.812 --> 18:47.731
You need to listen to this, you punk!

18:51.526 --> 18:53.195
-Can you charge this?
-Yes, sir.

18:53.278 --> 18:56.073
He called out of the blue
and asked if I wanted a part-time job.

18:56.156 --> 18:58.450
I just had to wear a watch
and get 400,000 won per month.

18:58.533 --> 19:00.827
It was supposed to indicate
your emotional state

19:00.911 --> 19:02.955
and was in the final testing phase
before its launch.

19:03.038 --> 19:03.956
I thought it was great.

19:04.039 --> 19:04.873
So I went to the company.

19:04.957 --> 19:07.292
I signed a consent form, put on the watch,

19:07.376 --> 19:10.295
and was being trained on how to use it
when an employee suddenly came in

19:10.963 --> 19:12.756
and said there was a mistake.

19:13.799 --> 19:15.634
He said I wasn't eligible

19:16.301 --> 19:17.678
and that all the artist slots
have been filled in.

19:18.428 --> 19:19.513
So I said, "What do you mean?"

19:19.596 --> 19:21.473
"The development team leader
is my friend's younger brother,

19:21.556 --> 19:23.308
and I came because he said he needed me."

19:23.392 --> 19:26.228
But he said they needed
an unemployed man in his forties,

19:26.311 --> 19:29.523
and that was the person
they were expecting.

19:33.694 --> 19:34.528
You see,

19:35.904 --> 19:38.824
I wrote "film director"
in the occupation section.

19:39.408 --> 19:41.159
OCCUPATION: FILM DIRECTOR

19:42.327 --> 19:46.623
That's when my heart started pounding.

19:48.041 --> 19:51.211
I had no idea the word "unemployed"
would make my heart race like that.

19:52.337 --> 19:55.632
I'd never felt my heart
pound like that before.

19:56.133 --> 19:57.384
It still makes my heart pound.

19:57.467 --> 19:59.386
Whenever I hear the word "unemployed,"

20:00.429 --> 20:01.888
my heart pounds like this.

20:02.764 --> 20:03.765
My goodness.

20:03.849 --> 20:07.936
My heart rate was so high
that this thing beeped like crazy.

20:08.020 --> 20:10.647
All the employees came running in,

20:10.731 --> 20:13.275
and one of them even checked my pulse.

20:13.358 --> 20:15.694
Then I looked at the watch.

20:18.030 --> 20:19.281
Do you know what it said?

20:21.658 --> 20:22.993
"Deeply humiliated."

20:23.869 --> 20:26.538
DEEPLY HUMILIATED

20:27.539 --> 20:28.665
I felt…

20:30.167 --> 20:31.501
so damn humiliated.

20:38.550 --> 20:40.927
You made me feel deep humiliation,
you bastard.

20:41.011 --> 20:43.513
You thought I wouldn't find out
about you calling me

20:43.597 --> 20:45.474
an unemployed man in his forties?

20:45.557 --> 20:46.391
I'm sorry.

20:47.225 --> 20:48.518
I really messed up.

20:48.602 --> 20:51.021
How many times have you apologized so far?

20:51.104 --> 20:53.690
This device is scary as hell,

20:53.774 --> 20:55.609
but I'm wearing it
for the 400,000 won payments.

20:55.692 --> 20:57.694
I'll make you wear this one of these days.

20:57.778 --> 20:59.696
This is scarier than a lie detector.

20:59.780 --> 21:03.241
It pinpoints emotions
I didn't even know I had.

21:04.034 --> 21:05.702
It's insanely accurate.

21:05.786 --> 21:09.164
Once this hits the market,
you can kiss your relationships goodbye.

21:10.082 --> 21:12.000
Imagine you and your wife wearing this.

21:12.084 --> 21:14.669
You guys get by because you don't know
what the other person is really feeling.

21:14.753 --> 21:17.672
But imagine knowing that at every moment.

21:17.756 --> 21:18.799
"Displeasure."

21:19.633 --> 21:20.801
"Anger."

21:20.884 --> 21:22.010
"Desire to kill."

21:22.094 --> 21:25.514
You live fully exposed,
like you're emotionally naked.

21:26.723 --> 21:30.310
Then you'll come across a word
that makes your heart pound like me.

21:30.394 --> 21:31.728
Everyone has a word

21:32.229 --> 21:33.647
that makes their heart pound.

21:35.690 --> 21:36.733
You know what I mean.

21:36.817 --> 21:37.859
Adultery!

21:39.903 --> 21:43.448
Hey, someone's heart is racing right now.

21:43.532 --> 21:44.616
Affair!

21:44.699 --> 21:45.617
That's enough.

21:45.700 --> 21:46.952
-STD!
-Hey!

21:47.035 --> 21:49.413
Wow, you're really something.

21:51.373 --> 21:54.209
How do you tell the same story
like it's the first time?

21:54.292 --> 21:56.795
I've heard this exact story
at least five or six times.

21:56.878 --> 22:01.299
You messaged the group chat until dawn
the day you got that watch.

22:01.383 --> 22:03.093
How many more times do we have to hear it?

22:03.176 --> 22:04.970
I'm genuinely curious.

22:05.053 --> 22:07.806
Do you just forget you've told it?

22:08.640 --> 22:09.975
Or do you just keep going anyway?

22:10.809 --> 22:11.768
It's fun.

22:16.731 --> 22:18.066
It's fun!

22:20.110 --> 22:22.070
It's fun telling a good story again.

22:23.071 --> 22:24.781
It's fun the third and fourth time too!

22:28.118 --> 22:29.661
Don't you ever tell the same story?

22:45.260 --> 22:47.554
I'm going to tell this story forever.

22:50.640 --> 22:51.808
It's so much fun.

22:52.392 --> 22:53.310
It's better than a movie.

22:59.983 --> 23:00.984
You know what?

23:01.067 --> 23:03.737
If a movie is fun,
I'll watch it over and over.

23:03.820 --> 23:07.240
It's a hundred times better
than watching a boring new release!

23:22.047 --> 23:22.964
Dong-man.

23:23.882 --> 23:26.760
We're here to congratulate Director Park
on the release of his movie.

23:34.184 --> 23:35.143
Congrats!

23:43.485 --> 23:45.946
Come on, Gyeong-se.
The guest of honor can't take off first.

23:46.613 --> 23:48.615
I don't want to cause any trouble
before the release.

23:52.827 --> 23:54.162
Damn it.

23:54.829 --> 23:56.498
I'll see you after the release.

23:59.542 --> 24:01.920
It's been a while,
but he hasn't changed a bit.

24:02.545 --> 24:04.214
It's only been a while for you.

24:05.298 --> 24:07.384
We see him all the time.

24:08.051 --> 24:09.177
What's he doing these days?

24:09.761 --> 24:10.720
Is he even working?

24:11.304 --> 24:13.098
He teaches kids at an academy,

24:14.057 --> 24:16.393
but I hear he's not even making
a million won a month.

24:18.061 --> 24:19.229
Is he at least writing?

24:19.854 --> 24:20.772
I have no idea.

24:20.855 --> 24:22.607
Is he still working on that screenplay?

24:23.733 --> 24:25.360
Weather Maker.

24:28.613 --> 24:30.991
Shouldn't someone tell him?

24:34.577 --> 24:35.870
That it's time he gave up.

24:36.913 --> 24:39.624
Come on, how can we tell him that?

24:39.708 --> 24:41.376
You should tell him, Yeong-su.

24:41.918 --> 24:44.129
It won't hurt him as much if you say it.

24:44.212 --> 24:46.881
That's right. It won't hurt much
if it comes from you.

24:50.260 --> 24:51.845
But it'd hurt me to tell him.

24:51.928 --> 24:55.223
Please, please, please!

24:55.307 --> 24:57.892
Create art in your native language!

24:57.976 --> 24:58.935
You've seen it!

24:59.019 --> 25:01.146
It kills the vibe
when a foreign actor speaks Korean.

25:01.229 --> 25:02.147
It's the same thing.

25:02.230 --> 25:04.941
They get turned off
when we speak their language too.

25:05.525 --> 25:07.110
Your native language

25:07.736 --> 25:09.154
carries depth and soul.

25:09.237 --> 25:13.491
Actors have to pour their soul
into their acting, so why make them

25:13.575 --> 25:14.951
speak a foreign language?

25:15.035 --> 25:17.537
And yet you still want to
work with Tony Leung Chiu-wai?

25:17.620 --> 25:18.705
Tony Leung Chiu-wai

25:19.748 --> 25:20.999
can speak alien if he wants to.

25:26.838 --> 25:28.715
-He can do whatever he wants!
-Fair enough.

25:28.798 --> 25:31.468
-I'm going to take off.
-You're right, he can do whatever.

25:31.551 --> 25:33.386
What about Maggie Cheung?

25:33.470 --> 25:36.389
She definitely gets a pass.

25:36.473 --> 25:38.350
-What about Leslie Cheung?
-I said no!

25:38.433 --> 25:41.770
-What about Bruce Lee?
-No way.

25:44.272 --> 25:46.358
I have nothing but respect

25:47.817 --> 25:48.860
for Jun-hwan.

25:49.819 --> 25:51.196
I'm not the only one
who finds him difficult, right?

25:52.655 --> 25:54.491
Absolutely yes!

26:02.082 --> 26:04.876
Sorry for all the trouble,
Director Lee Jun-hwan.

26:06.378 --> 26:07.462
Just wait.

26:08.505 --> 26:11.132
My days of being treated like a nuisance
are almost over.

26:17.472 --> 26:18.431
You'll see.

26:19.516 --> 26:20.642
What is it?

26:21.393 --> 26:22.602
Later.

26:23.645 --> 26:24.896
I'll tell you later.

26:27.440 --> 26:29.067
You're going to the premiere, right?

26:29.150 --> 26:30.193
It's this Wednesday.

26:31.486 --> 26:32.529
Only if you're going.

26:33.321 --> 26:34.489
I won't go if you're not there.

26:36.741 --> 26:38.326
You know it's awkward
between me and the others.

26:50.797 --> 26:51.631
I caught it!

26:56.010 --> 26:57.387
How did I catch it?

26:57.971 --> 26:59.681
-You do the weirdest things.
-I'm never letting this go.

27:05.478 --> 27:06.813
Why did you want me to read this?

27:08.398 --> 27:09.607
What did you like about it?

27:10.442 --> 27:12.569
There's a tearjerker scene later on.

27:13.653 --> 27:14.946
Where exactly is this scene?

27:15.864 --> 27:17.407
I didn't see it anywhere.

27:17.490 --> 27:18.741
All I felt was frustration.

27:19.534 --> 27:21.453
If we move up the scene in the latter half

27:21.536 --> 27:23.621
where the protagonist
starts pulling it together--

27:23.705 --> 27:25.373
This is the twelfth draft.

27:28.751 --> 27:31.838
If this is the result after 12 revisions,
there's no hope.

27:33.256 --> 27:34.215
Just trash it.

27:36.551 --> 27:38.470
Tell them we're ending their contract.

27:38.553 --> 27:40.054
And tell them

27:40.138 --> 27:44.934
this screenplay is a perfect example
of why people like them shouldn't write.

27:45.018 --> 27:46.936
Actually, just give it back to them.

27:47.645 --> 27:49.230
Tell them to hang it on the wall

27:49.314 --> 27:52.108
and look at it every time
they get the nerve to write again,

27:52.192 --> 27:54.569
instead of making busy people read it
and pissing them off!

27:56.070 --> 27:57.489
How frustrating.

28:04.412 --> 28:06.414
Hwang Dong-man is driving me crazy.

28:06.498 --> 28:09.292
I don't care about your emotional state.

28:10.710 --> 28:12.462
That damn emotion watch.

28:12.545 --> 28:15.256
He gives updates all day
in the group chat.

28:15.340 --> 28:19.052
I look away for a bit,
and he's already sent 30 to 40 messages.

28:19.135 --> 28:20.929
As if anyone cares about him.

28:21.012 --> 28:23.306
He's doing that
precisely because nobody cares.

28:24.015 --> 28:25.433
He's like a walking corpse.

28:26.309 --> 28:28.728
It's like what the kid
in The Sixth Sense said.

28:28.811 --> 28:31.814
"They don't know they're dead."

28:31.898 --> 28:34.317
Like Hwang Dong-man doesn't know
he's dead either.

28:35.401 --> 28:38.571
At this point,
I think you're the ones to blame.

28:40.031 --> 28:41.032
Let me ask you something.

28:41.533 --> 28:42.825
Do you think Hwang Dong-man

28:43.326 --> 28:44.536
has a chance to debut?

28:48.832 --> 28:51.751
Then do you think
he will willingly leave the film industry?

28:54.087 --> 28:55.129
He won't.

28:56.130 --> 29:00.844
He'll continue to hang around,
pretending to be part of the industry.

29:01.511 --> 29:06.307
He's counting on people being too polite
to say it to his face,

29:06.391 --> 29:09.394
and he's going to keep acting
like he's some big shot.

29:11.813 --> 29:15.525
As a crusader for cutting ties,
I've preached this message so many times.

29:16.901 --> 29:20.238
So why can't any of you cut ties
with the person who deserves it the most?

29:20.321 --> 29:22.448
Who cares if you went to college together?

29:23.575 --> 29:25.535
I've said this a million times.

29:26.369 --> 29:29.914
What happens when you cut off
98% of your relationships?

29:29.998 --> 29:31.583
Nothing. No problem at all.

29:31.666 --> 29:34.460
It's hard enough
even if you're around competent people.

29:34.544 --> 29:35.837
Cut ties!

29:35.920 --> 29:36.880
Cut ties.

29:36.963 --> 29:39.299
I have a lot of people
to cut ties with this year.

29:39.382 --> 29:43.011
They'll need to prove
why I should keep them around.

29:43.511 --> 29:45.847
If they don't, it won't end well.

29:45.930 --> 29:46.931
Trash it.

29:58.610 --> 30:00.820
That was really mean, wasn't it?

30:02.864 --> 30:04.741
How could she call him a walking corpse?

30:04.824 --> 30:07.452
Producer Choi Hyo-jin is a jerk overall,

30:08.328 --> 30:10.038
but sometimes her analogies are amazing.

30:10.121 --> 30:14.000
I went to a premiere after-party once
and joined their table.

30:14.083 --> 30:16.336
When Hwang Dong-man started talking,
that was it.

30:16.920 --> 30:18.671
Nobody responded to him at all.

30:19.422 --> 30:21.299
Even at their age,
they were leaving him out.

30:21.925 --> 30:23.801
I had a rough time
being the only one responding to him.

30:30.183 --> 30:31.476
Here's your food.

30:32.393 --> 30:33.227
It's our tteokbokki.

30:35.813 --> 30:36.731
Thank you.

30:38.608 --> 30:39.651
What should I eat first?

31:00.672 --> 31:03.967
Open the door already.

31:04.050 --> 31:06.636
Open the door.

31:06.719 --> 31:09.013
Open the door.

31:09.097 --> 31:10.932
Open the damn door!

31:11.015 --> 31:13.893
I said open the damn door already!

31:55.226 --> 31:56.352
You scared me.

31:56.436 --> 31:58.104
Why the hell did you come in so quietly?

31:58.187 --> 32:00.481
Do I have to report to you
to enter my own house?

32:02.025 --> 32:03.443
Why is the maintenance fee overdue?

32:09.115 --> 32:10.700
You said you'd pay it.

32:13.494 --> 32:14.328
I will.

32:14.412 --> 32:15.830
Then why is it overdue?

32:15.913 --> 32:16.998
I said I'll pay it!

32:21.502 --> 32:23.671
All you do is watch movies at home.

32:36.350 --> 32:38.186
SCREENWRITING WORKBOOK

32:56.913 --> 32:58.706
Don't drink on an empty stomach.

32:59.999 --> 33:02.794
I talked to the guys at the site,
so come with me starting next week.

33:03.878 --> 33:05.046
Welding is easy to pick up.

33:05.922 --> 33:08.841
Learn the job first
and take your time getting certified.

33:08.925 --> 33:11.052
Forget it. I told you I'm not doing it.

33:11.135 --> 33:13.304
How long are you going to
lounge around at home?

33:13.387 --> 33:15.431
I'm not lounging around.

33:16.224 --> 33:17.767
I'm brainstorming!

33:17.850 --> 33:19.477
You think writing comes that easy?

33:20.520 --> 33:21.562
Everyone works like me!

33:21.646 --> 33:23.689
Making one film every five or ten years!

33:23.773 --> 33:25.191
One every five or ten years?

33:25.274 --> 33:27.068
That's not work! That's a hobby!

33:27.693 --> 33:32.240
Real work is when you wake up, wash up,
get out there, grit your teeth,

33:32.323 --> 33:34.117
-and die trying!
-I'm already doing that!

33:34.200 --> 33:35.034
Every day!

33:35.952 --> 33:36.786
Until you make it!

33:36.869 --> 33:38.871
If I die trying every day,
I'll actually die!

33:50.299 --> 33:52.176
I made it to the final round!

33:53.094 --> 33:54.345
I'm almost there!

34:00.560 --> 34:01.853
Why did you make me say it?

34:02.436 --> 34:03.479
It's bad luck!

34:04.105 --> 34:05.773
I've kept my mouth shut until now!

34:17.493 --> 34:18.536
Have a nice day.

34:34.051 --> 34:35.845
I can't believe you said that!

34:35.928 --> 34:37.180
-Goodbye, Mr. Hwang!
-Goodbye, sir!

34:37.263 --> 34:38.848
Bye, guys. Hey, Myeong-hun.

34:43.519 --> 34:44.395
You've got this.

34:45.354 --> 34:46.272
I've got this.

35:33.152 --> 35:34.820
-Hello.
-Hello.

35:43.120 --> 35:43.955
Getting off work?

35:44.747 --> 35:45.581
Yes.

35:49.543 --> 35:50.503
You got off work early.

35:51.671 --> 35:52.505
Yes.

36:08.187 --> 36:10.773
It looks like a cigarette burn,
but it's actually a bullet hole.

36:13.317 --> 36:14.694
I didn't get shot.

36:16.904 --> 36:19.782
It was worn by a Russian soldier
during World War II.

36:20.783 --> 36:22.535
He'd have died if he got shot here, right?

36:25.663 --> 36:28.291
I bought this at a flea market
when I went to the Berlin Film Festival,

36:28.374 --> 36:30.501
but it's so heavy that
I get exhausted after ten minutes.

36:33.129 --> 36:34.046
But still,

36:34.130 --> 36:37.091
when I wear the clothes of someone
who stood in the center of world history,

36:37.883 --> 36:39.218
it feels like

36:39.844 --> 36:42.471
I can step right into
the center of history myself.

36:45.808 --> 36:49.895
But isn't it tragic, wearing the clothes
of someone who was shot and killed?

36:54.066 --> 36:56.319
Well, even if it's tragic,

36:56.402 --> 36:57.945
it's still in the center.

37:07.538 --> 37:09.040
You seem to be in a good mood.

37:10.124 --> 37:11.709
I'm on my way home from a lecture.

37:12.335 --> 37:13.794
I'm always full of energy afterward.

37:14.754 --> 37:16.630
You must find teaching rewarding.

37:16.714 --> 37:18.924
No. Talking gives me energy.

37:21.510 --> 37:24.513
I feel awake
when my voice resonates through my body.

37:24.597 --> 37:26.515
It's like the vibration of my own voice

37:27.099 --> 37:28.976
wakes me up or something.

37:30.603 --> 37:33.230
When I talk for an hour
without anyone interrupting me,

37:33.731 --> 37:36.567
I feel completely recharged.

37:48.287 --> 37:49.872
If I have nobody to talk to,

37:50.456 --> 37:52.416
I go to the rooftop and shout my name.

37:58.089 --> 37:59.799
Hey, Dong-man!

38:02.510 --> 38:04.095
Hwang Dong-man!

38:06.847 --> 38:08.557
Dong-man!

38:10.476 --> 38:12.353
Hwang Dong-man!

38:14.814 --> 38:16.690
Everything my voice reaches is mine.

38:18.651 --> 38:19.777
That tree is mine.

38:20.277 --> 38:21.445
That boulder is mine.

38:22.613 --> 38:23.948
It's about projecting myself.

38:26.534 --> 38:27.993
Once my voice reaches something…

38:30.955 --> 38:33.833
it no longer feels
completely unrelated to me.

38:36.544 --> 38:38.671
That's how it feels.

38:41.424 --> 38:42.508
Yeah, that's it.

38:46.846 --> 38:47.680
I heard you.

38:51.225 --> 38:52.977
I heard you shouting, "Hey, Dong-man!"

39:07.158 --> 39:08.159
Mine.

39:08.242 --> 39:10.035
Oh gosh, I'm sorry.

39:10.119 --> 39:11.787
I'm sorry. It was a joke. Really.

39:11.871 --> 39:12.746
I just…

39:13.581 --> 39:14.665
I'm really sorry.

39:16.876 --> 39:18.127
I'm sorry.

39:20.254 --> 39:22.381
Can you show me your screenplay?

39:25.885 --> 39:26.844
I'm curious.

40:17.645 --> 40:20.564
WE SELL GIMBAP

40:23.275 --> 40:24.151
Yes?

40:24.235 --> 40:25.069
Two rolls, please!

40:25.152 --> 40:26.403
Okay.

40:29.865 --> 40:30.699
Here you go.

40:31.659 --> 40:33.244
-Thank you.
-Have a good night.

40:33.327 --> 40:34.161
Goodbye.

40:34.245 --> 40:35.871
I'm home.

40:35.955 --> 40:37.373
Are you just getting in?

40:53.806 --> 40:55.099
Did he eat everything?

40:55.975 --> 40:56.976
Yes.

40:57.059 --> 40:59.311
Tell Jae-yeong to come over for a meal.

40:59.979 --> 41:00.980
Is he busy?

41:01.063 --> 41:02.565
He never comes over these days.

41:03.274 --> 41:04.191
He's busy.

41:08.195 --> 41:09.780
THE LOYAL CATERING

42:00.080 --> 42:02.458
How can you tell
if the world has ended or not?

42:03.876 --> 42:05.628
It comes down to the weather.

42:06.754 --> 42:08.672
As long as there are clouds in the sky,

42:09.506 --> 42:10.549
wind in the air,

42:11.258 --> 42:12.926
and leaves stirring in the breeze…

42:14.261 --> 42:15.763
As long as weather exists,

42:17.348 --> 42:19.058
the world hasn't ended.

42:29.401 --> 42:30.486
Dong-man.

42:30.569 --> 42:31.403
Dong-man.

42:32.112 --> 42:33.155
What?

42:37.618 --> 42:39.411
The movie, Weather Maker, is…

42:39.995 --> 42:41.872
Weather Maker is…

42:41.955 --> 42:44.083
In an age when weather has vanished…

42:44.166 --> 42:45.751
In an age when weather has vanished,

42:45.834 --> 42:47.795
he uses a weather-making machine…

42:49.505 --> 42:52.049
To bring the weather back to the world.

42:52.549 --> 42:53.634
To the world.

42:57.262 --> 43:00.057
This screenplay
relies heavily on the protagonist.

43:01.016 --> 43:03.519
Weather Maker is…

43:03.602 --> 43:05.312
It's a story about a man.

43:05.396 --> 43:06.897
Weather Maker is…

43:06.980 --> 43:10.859
It's a story about a man who fights
to bring weather back to the world.

43:22.996 --> 43:24.581
HWANG DONG-MAN
WEATHER MAKER

43:28.669 --> 43:31.171
2025 KOREAN FILM ASSOCIATION
MID-BUDGET KOREAN FILM PRODUCTION FUNDING

43:42.599 --> 43:43.976
Mr. Hwang Dong-man.

43:44.059 --> 43:44.893
Here.

44:05.664 --> 44:09.793
SISTER VENGEANCE
DIRECTOR PARK GYEONG-SE

44:22.139 --> 44:25.684
BLOODY REVENGE BEGINS TO RESCUE A SIBLING
SISTER VENGEANCE

44:28.395 --> 44:30.689
-This movie was insane.
-Did you like it?

44:30.773 --> 44:32.107
-It was amazing.
-Amazing, huh?

44:32.191 --> 44:34.943
I'm betting ten million at the box office.

44:38.822 --> 44:40.240
-Did you enjoy it?
-I really enjoyed it.

44:40.324 --> 44:41.700
You did? Come to the after-party.

44:41.784 --> 44:43.952
-See you at the after-party.
-Yes.

44:44.036 --> 44:45.662
We only contributed a bit.

44:45.746 --> 44:47.664
You're here! Producer Oh, I need you to…

44:47.748 --> 44:49.458
I'm a huge fan, Mi-ran.

44:49.541 --> 44:52.628
I hope we can work on
a good project together someday.

44:52.711 --> 44:56.340
All the luck to Sister Vengeance
and Director Park Gyeong-se!

44:56.924 --> 44:58.091
You're the best!

44:58.175 --> 45:00.010
Gyeong-se, drinks are on you
if the movie does well.

45:00.093 --> 45:02.221
But not at Agit. I'm not going there.

45:05.807 --> 45:08.310
All right, team. Cheers!

45:08.393 --> 45:10.354
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

45:10.437 --> 45:13.023
-Good work!
-Ten million!

45:14.066 --> 45:15.150
I just knew it.

45:18.362 --> 45:20.280
My blood pressure was through the roof
the entire two hours.

45:21.281 --> 45:23.700
There wasn't a single good scene or shot.

45:23.784 --> 45:26.286
I've seen shots like that a million times.

45:26.370 --> 45:28.121
It was great seeing them again, Gyeong-se.

45:28.205 --> 45:30.541
As usual, you half-assed it.

45:30.624 --> 45:32.334
Hey, keep your voice down.

45:33.168 --> 45:35.712
If I lower my voice,
it'll feel like I'm saying something bad.

45:35.796 --> 45:37.422
I don't feel guilty at all.

45:37.506 --> 45:40.008
Jang Mi-ran smacks her junior
on the back of the head and asks,

45:40.092 --> 45:42.427
"Hey, have you eaten yet?"

45:42.511 --> 45:45.722
Why do actresses get all weird
when they play detectives?

45:45.806 --> 45:47.307
They swagger too much.

45:47.391 --> 45:48.767
Is that what they teach in acting classes?

45:50.310 --> 45:51.436
I once saw a phone scene

45:51.520 --> 45:53.605
of an actor playing
the Seoul Counter-Terrorism Unit leader.

45:53.689 --> 45:55.357
He had a lisp.

45:55.440 --> 45:57.442
"I'm the head
of the Theoul Counter-Terrorithm Unit…"

45:57.526 --> 45:59.820
My heart dropped.
How could he give an order?

45:59.903 --> 46:01.822
What if they dropped a bomb
in the wrong place?

46:01.905 --> 46:03.615
"Theoul. Drop it in Theoul."

46:03.699 --> 46:05.033
"I said in Theoul."

46:05.117 --> 46:06.159
"Drop it in Theoul."

46:07.327 --> 46:11.206
He's not cruel or vicious,
so why does he try to write dark stories?

46:11.290 --> 46:14.251
He should stick to making lame movies,
just like him.

46:14.334 --> 46:15.586
Noir, my ass.

46:15.669 --> 46:17.713
He tried to make it appear stylish,

46:17.796 --> 46:19.881
but it was so tacky that I almost lost it.

46:19.965 --> 46:23.010
My emotion watch was red
during the entire movie.

46:23.093 --> 46:26.263
Remember what I told you?
Green means good, and red means bad.

46:26.346 --> 46:30.934
My watch kept vibrating and flashing red,
so I looked at it.

46:31.018 --> 46:35.022
"Bored, bored, bored, bored, annoyed,
annoyed, annoyed, annoyed, annoyed."

46:35.939 --> 46:37.733
For two whole hours.

46:39.276 --> 46:40.319
I thought it was fun.

46:45.365 --> 46:46.950
You thought it was fun?

46:47.618 --> 46:48.994
It was fun.

46:49.077 --> 46:51.622
It's not like he committed a huge crime.

46:51.705 --> 46:55.000
Why get so upset over a movie
just because you didn't enjoy it?

46:55.667 --> 46:57.878
Seung-tae, don't you get angry

46:58.503 --> 47:01.006
when you go to a restaurant
and the food is bad?

47:01.089 --> 47:02.549
It's the same thing.

47:02.633 --> 47:05.052
Watching a boring movie is exactly like

47:05.135 --> 47:07.554
going to a crappy restaurant
when you're starving!

47:08.597 --> 47:09.848
Why do we watch movies?

47:09.931 --> 47:13.060
It's like paying for a two-hour,
mood-lifting massage.

47:13.810 --> 47:15.395
To feel good, Seung-tae!

47:15.479 --> 47:16.730
Jeez, you're so frustrating.

47:19.983 --> 47:21.985
Doesn't he write comedies?

47:24.029 --> 47:25.447
Damn it.

47:25.530 --> 47:28.325
He shouldn't go around
and ruin the mood at every event.

47:28.408 --> 47:30.535
They all worked so damn hard
on this movie!

47:30.619 --> 47:32.579
It's because he's never done it before.

47:32.663 --> 47:33.580
Let's go.

47:38.168 --> 47:39.211
I just don't get it.

47:39.878 --> 47:41.505
-Hey!
-Hey.

48:02.901 --> 48:04.069
SISTER VENGEANCE

48:10.450 --> 48:13.161
You seem to have a lot of issues
with my acting.

48:14.746 --> 48:16.581
What have you worked on, Director?

48:19.459 --> 48:20.585
Well, I…

48:28.218 --> 48:29.886
You're going straight home, right?

48:39.187 --> 48:40.647
That damn nobody.

48:47.070 --> 48:49.322
I heard Ma Jae-yeong
got the film production funding.

48:50.741 --> 48:51.616
Really?

48:53.577 --> 48:55.245
Good for him.

48:56.037 --> 48:57.956
I heard the funding is pretty substantial.

48:58.039 --> 48:58.874
Three billion won.

48:59.499 --> 49:00.417
That's a lot.

49:00.500 --> 49:02.753
Things are finally
working out for him too.

49:03.503 --> 49:05.255
I knew Jae-yeong would get it.

49:05.338 --> 49:07.299
He has a certain appeal, you know.

49:07.382 --> 49:08.884
This might sound harsh,

49:08.967 --> 49:12.554
but if a person isn't appealing,
their writing won't be either.

49:23.315 --> 49:25.609
You're the most appealing person

49:26.234 --> 49:28.320
I've ever met.

49:29.321 --> 49:30.947
So what's wrong with your writing?

49:31.656 --> 49:33.283
You have so many women,

49:33.366 --> 49:35.243
and you're the most appealing man alive.

49:36.912 --> 49:38.497
So what's wrong with your writing?

49:59.810 --> 50:00.936
Let's go for a second round.

50:35.220 --> 50:36.805
-That little…
-Don't.

50:38.557 --> 50:41.643
When I saw that scene earlier,

50:41.726 --> 50:43.436
it just dawned on me.

50:43.520 --> 50:48.358
We could do a prequel with you
as the eldest sister, and…

50:48.441 --> 50:49.401
What the heck?

52:29.459 --> 52:33.338
If I can't prove myself by succeeding,
I'll prove myself by falling apart!

52:33.421 --> 52:36.007
If I can't prove myself by succeeding,

52:36.091 --> 52:38.176
I'll prove myself by falling apart!

52:38.259 --> 52:40.136
If I can't prove myself by succeeding…

52:48.979 --> 52:52.691
YOUR CURRENT SPEED
22 KM/H

53:38.987 --> 53:42.991
"Went for a mood-lifting massage,
but it only ruined my mood."

53:43.074 --> 53:44.325
That bastard.

53:44.409 --> 53:46.077
It might not be Dong-man.

53:46.161 --> 53:48.371
Look. Just take a look.

53:48.455 --> 53:50.248
The username is "muzik,"
which means "unemployed."

53:50.331 --> 53:52.125
The bastard's obsessed with that word.

53:53.543 --> 53:55.503
He just had to post on a major portal,
of all places.

53:55.587 --> 53:57.672
And look at the time.
It was right after the premiere.

53:59.382 --> 54:00.800
Damn it.

54:02.719 --> 54:04.429
Stuffing his face
through the entire movie.

54:04.512 --> 54:07.724
Have you ever seen someone in the industry
snacking on popcorn at a premiere?

54:09.059 --> 54:12.771
He kept crunching away
during the important scenes.

54:17.984 --> 54:18.985
The light's changing.

54:20.570 --> 54:21.571
Damn it.

54:22.155 --> 54:23.364
The light!

54:28.411 --> 54:29.537
My goodness.

54:31.039 --> 54:32.832
-What the heck?
-Jeez.

54:32.916 --> 54:34.250
That scared me.

54:35.919 --> 54:36.961
Sorry.

54:37.587 --> 54:38.421
I'm sorry.

54:48.014 --> 54:49.933
-Why, that little…
-Don't!

54:50.517 --> 54:51.976
Don't point your finger at me!

54:52.060 --> 54:54.104
I ought to break every last one!

54:55.563 --> 54:56.564
I'm sorry.

54:58.566 --> 54:59.567
Get in.

55:01.069 --> 55:03.404
Just look at that punk.

55:05.615 --> 55:07.325
Damn it!

55:07.408 --> 55:08.368
Hey!

55:09.536 --> 55:10.495
Hey!

55:16.835 --> 55:17.752
Honey!

55:18.336 --> 55:19.546
Honey!

55:20.338 --> 55:21.923
-Are you okay?
-Are you okay?

55:22.006 --> 55:23.800
-That must hurt really bad.
-Oh dear.

55:23.883 --> 55:25.176
He hit it really hard.

55:25.260 --> 55:27.095
-Shouldn't we do something?
-Is he okay?

55:27.178 --> 55:29.722
-How is he?
-He should go to a hospital.

55:30.348 --> 55:32.684
He's okay. He's fine.

55:33.643 --> 55:35.728
Get up. Honey, get up.

55:35.812 --> 55:37.605
Park Gyeong-se, get up.

55:37.689 --> 55:38.523
I said get up.

55:43.236 --> 55:45.363
I'll tell them to do the stage greeting
without you.

55:45.446 --> 55:48.032
Don't worry about it,
and just take care of yourself.

55:49.784 --> 55:50.618
Okay.

55:58.668 --> 56:00.753
Let's see here…

56:02.005 --> 56:04.215
LOAN SHARK

56:46.090 --> 56:47.175
Fuck!

57:03.858 --> 57:06.152
How can you tell
if the world has ended or not?

57:07.278 --> 57:08.947
It comes down to the weather.

57:10.490 --> 57:12.909
When depression pressed down on me
like a heavy iron weight,

57:13.534 --> 57:15.119
and I couldn't even sit up,

57:16.537 --> 57:17.956
all I wanted…

57:19.207 --> 57:20.291
was weather.

57:22.585 --> 57:23.878
If only the weather could change…

57:25.922 --> 57:29.050
If only there were a machine
that could create any type of weather…

57:30.426 --> 57:31.344
I wonder

57:32.095 --> 57:33.930
what kind of weather I'd create right now.

58:53.468 --> 58:57.305
WEATHER MAKER

58:57.388 --> 58:58.806
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

59:40.306 --> 59:41.307
Hello?

59:41.391 --> 59:42.892
I'm off now.

59:42.975 --> 59:44.227
Hello.

59:45.812 --> 59:46.854
It's really good.

59:48.439 --> 59:49.273
Hey.

59:50.066 --> 59:50.900
Come on in.

59:54.195 --> 59:56.614
I heard you asked one of my employees
to look at your screenplay.

59:57.156 --> 59:57.990
I did.

01:00:04.288 --> 01:00:05.248
It's very nice here.

01:00:05.832 --> 01:00:06.916
-Take a seat.
-Okay.

01:00:10.336 --> 01:00:11.170
Ax, come in here.

01:00:14.382 --> 01:00:15.341
Come on.

01:00:30.440 --> 01:00:32.984
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

01:00:36.112 --> 01:00:38.948
So rumor has it that I don't make the call
on the films we produce,

01:00:40.158 --> 01:00:42.034
but she does.

01:00:44.746 --> 01:00:47.457
It's my call. Choi Dong-hyeon's call.

01:00:47.540 --> 01:00:48.374
Right.

01:00:49.083 --> 01:00:51.711
I can't read every screenplay
that comes flooding in,

01:00:51.794 --> 01:00:53.838
so she goes through them first

01:00:53.921 --> 01:00:57.508
and puts only the ones
I should read on my desk.

01:00:58.384 --> 01:01:01.679
Now, let's see whether
I need to read yours or not.

01:01:03.639 --> 01:01:04.932
Let's listen to what she says.

01:01:05.892 --> 01:01:08.686
You used to be famous for hacking through
screenplays like an ax,

01:01:09.228 --> 01:01:11.105
but not so sharp these days.

01:01:14.192 --> 01:01:15.485
You still got that edge?

01:01:18.529 --> 01:01:19.572
Hack into it.

01:01:23.326 --> 01:01:24.160
Get started.

01:01:24.827 --> 01:01:25.745
It's just us here.

01:01:30.416 --> 01:01:31.542
What are you waiting for?

01:01:35.922 --> 01:01:38.299
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

01:01:41.886 --> 01:01:43.679
"A story about a man who fights against AI

01:01:44.180 --> 01:01:46.557
to bring weather back in a future world

01:01:47.475 --> 01:01:49.811
where weather no longer exists."

01:01:50.436 --> 01:01:51.395
This is

01:01:52.647 --> 01:01:54.273
what your one-line logline says.

01:01:56.400 --> 01:01:57.860
But he doesn't really fight.

01:02:00.905 --> 01:02:02.657
The antagonist should stand strong,

01:02:02.740 --> 01:02:04.700
and the protagonist should stand
just as strong,

01:02:04.784 --> 01:02:06.118
and the two should clash.

01:02:06.202 --> 01:02:08.204
But both the antagonist and protagonist
come off as indecisive.

01:02:09.914 --> 01:02:11.165
Most importantly,

01:02:11.749 --> 01:02:13.501
the protagonist has no power.

01:02:15.002 --> 01:02:17.338
People crave power.

01:02:17.880 --> 01:02:19.507
Every single person.

01:02:20.800 --> 01:02:22.969
That's why they want a protagonist
who can survive any situation,

01:02:23.761 --> 01:02:25.763
never gets exhausted,

01:02:26.681 --> 01:02:28.933
pushes through challenges confidently,

01:02:29.559 --> 01:02:32.603
and comes out on top
like it's the most natural thing.

01:02:37.650 --> 01:02:40.820
They want to experience
that epic, explosive moment.

01:02:43.114 --> 01:02:44.282
But your protagonist?

01:02:46.033 --> 01:02:47.159
Nothing like that.

01:02:49.370 --> 01:02:52.164
You should've created a person with power.

01:02:54.250 --> 01:02:55.710
So why didn't you?

01:02:58.963 --> 01:03:00.423
Because the writer himself…

01:03:07.972 --> 01:03:09.223
doesn't have it in him.

01:03:10.349 --> 01:03:11.767
What did I do wrong?

01:03:12.810 --> 01:03:15.146
I'm tired of you getting hurt
over every little thing.

01:03:16.147 --> 01:03:17.189
When have I ever--

01:03:17.273 --> 01:03:19.150
You think you're hiding it,
but it's obvious.

01:03:19.734 --> 01:03:22.278
You make me feel guilty,
like I've done something terrible.

01:03:22.862 --> 01:03:25.656
I end up getting hurt
because you're always getting hurt.

01:03:27.867 --> 01:03:28.951
Why do we make movies?

01:03:30.161 --> 01:03:34.040
It's because we want to see
people with power.

01:03:34.123 --> 01:03:35.666
Why do you think we want to see that?

01:03:35.750 --> 01:03:37.418
Because we don't have power!

01:03:48.095 --> 01:03:50.139
YOUR CURRENT SPEED
20 KM/H

01:03:53.309 --> 01:03:54.310
A creator

01:03:55.186 --> 01:03:57.104
can't create what they don't possess.

01:04:24.966 --> 01:04:26.467
So I don't need to read it, right?

01:05:05.256 --> 01:05:06.132
Dong-man.

01:05:07.508 --> 01:05:08.634
Let me ask you something.

01:05:10.177 --> 01:05:11.762
Why do you think
it's not working out for you?

01:05:12.888 --> 01:05:15.141
I want to know your honest thoughts,

01:05:15.224 --> 01:05:16.225
so let's hear it.

01:05:17.226 --> 01:05:19.687
It's been 20 years.
Why do you think you haven't made it yet?

01:05:25.818 --> 01:05:26.777
I asked you a question.

01:05:30.281 --> 01:05:32.742
Nobody will say this to you.

01:05:32.825 --> 01:05:33.951
Not a single person.

01:05:34.910 --> 01:05:35.745
So,

01:05:36.704 --> 01:05:38.289
I'll step up and speak for everyone.

01:06:00.269 --> 01:06:02.104
You crazy bastard! What are you doing?

01:06:13.199 --> 01:06:14.241
It's time to give up.

01:06:15.743 --> 01:06:18.162
How long will you pursue something
that's not working?

01:06:18.746 --> 01:06:21.415
Don't make too much of those 20 years.

01:06:21.499 --> 01:06:23.584
If you'd gritted your teeth
and gone all in,

01:06:23.667 --> 01:06:25.461
you would've made it in ten years.

01:06:25.544 --> 01:06:28.172
But you just let 20 years slip by,

01:06:28.255 --> 01:06:30.925
just eating and shitting repeatedly.

01:06:38.891 --> 01:06:42.478
HUNGRY

01:07:09.755 --> 01:07:13.050
AGIT

01:07:15.553 --> 01:07:17.596
Someone had to tell him at some point.

01:07:17.680 --> 01:07:19.765
It's not like we didn't want to tell him.

01:07:20.683 --> 01:07:21.725
We just couldn't do it.

01:07:23.144 --> 01:07:25.646
It drives him insane
whenever someone is doing well.

01:07:25.729 --> 01:07:29.817
I mean, the guy leaves over 100 messages
in our group chat in a day,

01:07:30.442 --> 01:07:33.445
but doesn't say a word to congratulate me
on my film hitting a million.

01:07:33.529 --> 01:07:35.739
That's how selfish the bastard is.

01:07:35.823 --> 01:07:38.033
You saw
how he treated Jun-hwan last night.

01:07:38.117 --> 01:07:40.035
"So what's wrong with your writing?"

01:07:40.119 --> 01:07:41.412
What kind of person says that?

01:07:42.580 --> 01:07:43.497
Whatever.

01:07:44.248 --> 01:07:46.750
Hwang Dong-man just heard
what was coming to him.

01:07:49.420 --> 01:07:51.630
Whenever he saw me
after my movie was released,

01:07:51.714 --> 01:07:54.508
he'd say, "That's not a good movie."

01:07:55.342 --> 01:07:57.511
Why doesn't he make his own, then?

01:07:58.095 --> 01:08:01.432
He hasn't made a single movie,
yet he's always lecturing his juniors.

01:08:01.515 --> 01:08:03.058
Forget everything else.

01:08:03.142 --> 01:08:04.935
I just want him to shut up.

01:08:05.019 --> 01:08:07.229
He talks nonstop,
so nobody can get a word in.

01:08:07.313 --> 01:08:09.481
I feel like I'm going to lose my mind
listening to him.

01:08:09.565 --> 01:08:12.193
Can't he just stay quiet? Is that so hard?

01:08:12.276 --> 01:08:13.694
How can he stay quiet?

01:08:13.777 --> 01:08:14.904
He's terrified.

01:08:35.216 --> 01:08:36.592
If he doesn't say anything,

01:08:37.468 --> 01:08:39.094
he'd feel like he doesn't even exist.

01:08:40.054 --> 01:08:41.263
So how could he stay quiet?

01:09:29.103 --> 01:09:30.813
Instead of holding onto
what won't work out

01:09:30.896 --> 01:09:32.731
and getting jealous
of other people's success,

01:09:32.815 --> 01:09:34.400
start living more constructively

01:09:35.484 --> 01:09:36.944
and productively from now on.

01:09:42.658 --> 01:09:43.575
Okay?

01:09:48.330 --> 01:09:50.416
Why the hell does my life
have to please you, sir?

01:09:57.589 --> 01:09:59.508
You crazy bastard! What are you doing?

01:10:10.394 --> 01:10:11.562
Bravo!

01:10:15.357 --> 01:10:16.191
Sorry.

01:10:19.945 --> 01:10:23.240
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

01:10:42.426 --> 01:10:43.677
Did you get beaten up?

01:10:43.761 --> 01:10:45.179
Then what's with the cast?

01:10:45.262 --> 01:10:47.389
Hey, Dong-man!

01:10:48.390 --> 01:10:50.100
I said go and print it out!

01:10:50.184 --> 01:10:52.895
I feel for her,
but she has to handle it on her own.

01:10:53.562 --> 01:10:57.399
How should we describe the emotion
you feel when you get nosebleeds?

01:10:57.483 --> 01:10:58.317
You bastard!

01:10:58.400 --> 01:11:01.445
You know what I mean.
He ruins everything wherever he goes.

01:11:01.528 --> 01:11:03.197
You're not allowed to come here anymore.

01:11:03.280 --> 01:11:06.408
Adults call it cutting ties.

01:11:06.492 --> 01:11:08.952
Cutting ties as a group
is called bullying, you bastard!

01:11:09.036 --> 01:11:11.997
Why do you all find Director Hwang
so hard to deal with?

01:11:12.081 --> 01:11:14.083
How do people gain power?

01:11:15.918 --> 01:11:17.294
Maybe if you love someone…

01:11:17.878 --> 01:11:19.546
His heart would race.

01:11:21.298 --> 01:11:26.303
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
